Russian Equity Movers: Evraz, Raspadskaya, Sberbank, Uralkali

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-07-13T15:41:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/russian-equity-movers-evraz-raspadskaya-sberbank-uralkali.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  climbed 0.5
percent to 1,714.19 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, a second
day of gains. The dollar-denominated RTS Index rallied 1 percent
to 1,936.42.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Evraz Group SA (EVR LI), the Russian steelmaker which owns
a 40 percent stake in the OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX) coal miner,
climbed to the highest close since June 14, increasing 1.1
percent to $33.17 in London trading. State-run VEB bank may pay
$5.3 billion for an 80 percent stake in Raspadskaya, Interfax
said yesterday.  Raspadskaya climbed for a second day on the report, adding
1.1 percent to 180.47 rubles after a 2.8 percent gain yesterday.  OAO Sberbank (SBER03 RX) advanced for a second day, rising
1.4 percent to 103.94 rubles after  Russia ’s largest lender said
first-half profit almost tripled as the bank recovered reserves
set aside earlier for bad loans.  OAO Uralkali (URKA RX), Russia’s largest potash producer,
climbed to the highest closing price since August 2008 after the
company said anti-dumping measures for potassium chloride
deliveries to European Union countries have expired. The shares
increased 3.5 percent to 268.41 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
